This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the application of Anderson acceleration to value iteration, which is a common algorithm used in reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper also discusses how this idea could be applied more generally to (deep) reinforcement learning, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves numerical methods and algorithms, which could place it under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
